{
  "texts": [
    "Recognizing this limitation, recent researches have shifted towards a multi-time retrieval framework [1,15,21,26,34].",
    "This method doesn't confine knowledge retrieval to one instance but revisits it iteratively during the generation process, by decomposing the primary question into sub-questions [16], or leveraging partially generated content [25,39] and forward-looking sentences [12] as dynamic search queries.Although previous methods have made strides in improving the quality of generated answers, they strictly adhere to predefined reasoning steps over all questions.",
    "Such inflexible approaches lack the ability to diagnose specific errors in their responses and consequently don't possess mechanisms to enhance their performance.",
    "We argue that this limitation might stem from the model's lack of awareness regarding its own reasoning processes.",
    "When humans confront complex issues, they often reflect on their thought patterns, gradually adjusting and optimizing their strategies."
  ]
}